history.content:
Btw, are Math 53 and math 110 strict prereqs for CS189? Is it OK that I take Math 53 and CS 189 concurrently?

==================

53 should be a prereq but not strict if have learn partial differentiation well. It's basically impossible to take 189 in summer with any other commitment according to last summer.

110 is not strictly required either, if you have taken ee16AB or 54+ee16b and 70, but maturity is required. It's a very different perspective of linear algbra and probability, proof vs. calculation and many people dropped it even when they have taken 5354. I got A+ in ee series but still had a struggle at the beginning of it.

 

Last summer's 189 was basically Sahai's version with homework reduced in half. Many topics involve a lot of taking derivatives of one matrix with respect to another matrix so mathematical maturity is important. 

If you are not prepared and is not in junior or senior year, I would highly recommend you rethink about taking 189 in summer with the background you described, not because you cannot take it without a bunch of preparation classes, but because if you do not have a good understanding of these topics and take 189, it would be like eating a banquet in a fast food manner. That is, you will have 189 on your transcript but didn't really get its value, miss many important skills which are very very useful in career/research.
